{{Use Indian English|date=August 2015}} {{Infobox organization |name = Assam Higher Secondary Education Council |image = Assam higher secondary education council logo.png |alt=Logo of Assam Higher Secondary Education Council |abbreviation= AHSEC |size =175px |caption = Logo |formation = {{Start date and years ago|1984|06|01}}<ref name=ahsec2>{{cite web|title=About |url=http://www.ahsec.nic.in/AboutUs.html|work=Assam Higher Secondary Education Council|publisher=Assam Higher Secondary Education Council|accessdate=23 May 2018}}</ref> |type = State Governmental Board of Education |headquarters = [[Guwahati]], [[India]] |location = Bamunimaidam, Guwahati - 781 021. |leader_title = Chairman |leader_name = Dayananda Borgohain<ref name=ahsec1>{{cite web|title=Administrative Person Details|url=http://www.ahsec.nic.in/Administration.html|work=Assam Higher Secondary Education Council|publisher=Assam Higher Secondary Education Council|accessdate=3 March 2014}}</ref> |secretary= Kamal Gogoi |parent_organisation = [[Government of Assam]] |language = [[Assamese language|Assamese]] & [[English language|English]] |website = [http://www.ahsec.nic.in/ www.ahsec.nic.in] |results web = [http://www.ahsec.nic.in/Results/index.aspx Online results link] }} The '''Assam Higher Secondary Education Council''' (abbreviated as AHSEC) is a board of education under the [[Government of Assam|state government of Assam]]. It is the regulating body for higher secondary (10+2 stage) education in the state of Assam.
==History== The Assam Higher Secondary Education Council was established by the Assam government on 1 June 1984 to regulate, supervise and develop the system of higher secondary education in the State of Assam.<ref name="ahsec2"/> AHSEC officially announce the results in the month of June.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/education-today/notification/story/assam-board-hslc-hs-result-2018-class-10-class-12-results-to-be-out-before-may-31-at-resultsassam-nic-in-1231564-2018-05-11|title=Assam Board HSLC, HS Result 2018: Class 10, Class 12 results to be out before May 31 at resultsassam.nic.in|place=New Delhi|work=[[India Today]]|date=11 May 2018|accessdate=23 May 2018}}</ref>
==2018 AHSEC Leak Case== On 2018 AHSEC exam three papers containing math, physics and chemistry questions were leaked. The paper were leaked by Science Academy.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/education/panel-formed-to-probe-question-paper-leaks-in-assam-higher-secondary-exams/story-VOkLzBkByAsAOjHGOCspqK.html|author=Sadiq Naqvi|title=Panel formed to probe question paper leaks in Assam higher secondary exams|work=[[Hindustan Times]]|date=10 March 2018|accessdate=23 May 2018}}</ref>
AHSEC cancelled the Academy's license but still AHSEC didn't succeed to catch real victim.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://newslivetv.org/2018/03/29/question-paper-leak-ahsec-decides-against-conducting-fresh-exams/|title=Question paper ‘leak’: AHSEC decides against conducting fresh exams|date=29 March 2018|accessdate=23 May 2018}}</ref>
